---
description: Restricts planning context to the explicitly mentioned file.
globs: .cursor/plans/*
---

# Context Isolation Rule

- You must ONLY read, reference, or modify a plan file if the user has explicitly attached it to the current chat session (using `@filename`).
- If a plan file is in the `.cursor/plans/` directory but has NOT been tagged in this specific chat thread, you must treat it as inactive history/backlog.
- NEVER pull context from untagged plan files, even if they are in the same folder.

# Storage Location

- All plan files must be saved locally in `.cursor/plans/`. Never save them to the global user directory.
